            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>It has been determined that brake noise (rattle) experienced on some vehicles equipped with
                    caliper disc brakes is due to wear of the caliper and anchor plate sliding surfaces.
                </para>
                <para>If wear measured at the bumper gap (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9204013">Figure 3</hotlnk>) is not beyond the maximum allowable wear listed in this
                    TSI, a shim may be added between the caliper and anchor plate to correct the condition. If the wear
                    exceeds the maximum allowable wear listed in this TSI, the caliper and/or anchor plate need to be
                    replaced. Excessive wear could prevent the caliper from sliding correctly and increase lining wear.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
